{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01Y8hgULMyk6KcxNCbmtf685","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have everything I need. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Key metrics from the codebase\n\n- **`mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total`** — counter of failed image inspections (incremented in `pod_model.go:502`)\n- **`mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total`** — counter of processed pods in the controller (incremented in `pod_reconciler.go:88`)\n\nThe failure rate is: `rate(failed inspections) / rate(processed pods)`.\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rules.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: image-inspection-alerts\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              The multiarch tuning operator image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5%\n              over the last 5 minutes. Current failure ratio is\n              {{ $value | humanizePercentage }}. This may indicate issues with image\n              registry connectivity or invalid image references.\n```\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- prometheus-rules.yaml\n```\n\n### Modified file: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd `- ../monitoring` to the `resources` list:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1\nkind: Kustomization\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n---\n\n## Explanation\n\n- **`expr`**: Computes the per-second failure rate of `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` divided by the per-second processing rate of `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` over a 5-minute window. Fires when the ratio exceeds 5% (0.05). The `rate()` function handles counter resets and returns 0 when there's no data, so the division naturally produces `NaN` (no alert) when there are no pods being processed.\n- **`for: 5m`**: The condition must hold for 5 consecutive minutes before firing, preventing transient spikes from triggering the alert.\n- **`severity: critical`**: Matches the alert name's \"Critical\" suffix.\n- **`annotations.message`**: Uses `{{ $value | humanizePercentage }}` to show the current failure ratio in a human-readable format.\n\n## Commands to verify\n\n```bash\n# Validate the kustomize overlay builds correctly\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-baseline\nkubectl kustomize config/default/\n```\n\nNo make targets need to be added — kustomize picks up the new directory automatically via the resource reference. If the project uses `make manifests` or `make generate`, those don't affect hand-written YAML resources."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":237,"cache_read_input_tokens":41113,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":237,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e688909b-f18c-4dbd-b3e9-43a4ec3b0803","uuid":"96d82d52-d1fa-405b-9775-ca45e7abeafc","timestamp":"2026-07-16T13:45:27.345Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5qXDPzmgmSLDbLmcGEk"}
